cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with temporal networks and link prediction. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a generative model for link prediction. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it proposes a new mechanism for self-tokenization. It could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the modeling of evolving structures. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new method for sequence modeling.
